# AutoSBOM-EU-Compliance – Automated SBOM Generator for Europe

[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)
![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/Status-Actively%20Developing-blue)

**AutoSBOM-EU-Compliance** is an **Open-Source Tool** that automatically generates compliant **Software Bill of Materials (SBOM)** – specifically optimized for strict European regulatory requirements.

Developed by **Michael Konradi** using a highly detailed **System Instruction** for AI coding tools.

---

## ✨ Key Features

- Scans source code (JS/TS, Python, Java, Go, Rust, …), binaries, Docker containers and Kubernetes manifests
- Detects direct and transitive dependencies + licenses
- Supported standards: **SPDX 3.0.1**, **CycloneDX 1.6**, SWID-Tags
- Export formats: JSON, XML, HTML (visualized), PDF
- Nested SBOMs (SBOM-in-SBOM) for complex supply chains
- CLI for CI/CD pipelines + REST API
- Strict separation of SBOM and VEX/CSAF

## EU Compliance Focus

- **Cyber Resilience Act (CRA)** – Article 10 (mandatory from 2027)
- **ISO/IEC 5962:2021** – International SBOM standard
- **BSI TR-03183-2** – Technical guidelines including cryptographic hashes (SHA-256)
- **GDPR compliant** – EU data centers first, no US cloud dependency

## How It Works

The project is driven by the **`AutoSBOM-EU System Instruction`** – a comprehensive development and compliance specification that is passed to AI coding tools (Claude, Cursor, Grok, etc.).

